Package ac.code.verifier.processors

Class PropertyProcessor

java.lang.Object
javax.annotation.processing.AbstractProcessor
ac.code.verifier.processors.PropertyProcessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Processor
Direct Known Subclasses:
CodeFragmentPropertyProcessor, MethodRefactorabilityPropertyProcessor, MovableMethodPropertyProcessor
public abstract class PropertyProcessor extends AbstractProcessor
The class PropertyProcessor defines the capabilities common to all processors that check the existence of certain properties in the annotated code.

  • Method Details

    • process

      public boolean process(Set<? extends TypeElement> annotations, RoundEnvironment roundEnv)
      The method checks whether the code contains an annotation. If so, call the abstract method verifyFile (which checks whether the marked code fulfills the desired properties) and pass as parameters the annotation and the path of the source code. If a violation of the properties is detected - reports a compilation error.
      Specified by:
      process in interface Processor
      Specified by:
      process in class AbstractProcessor
      Parameters:
      annotations - The annotation types requested to be processed
      roundEnv - Environment for information about the current and prior round
      Returns:
      Whether or not the set of annotation types are claimed by this processor
